      <h2 class="center">RIGHT SIDE TECHNOLOGIES<br>PRIVACY POLICY</h2>
			<p><span class="underline">Effective Date</span>: January 16, 2014</p>
			<p>Welcome to Right Side Technologies! This Privacy Policy (this “Policy”) describes how Right Side Technologies, Inc. (“Right Side”, “we”, “our” or “us”) treats information collected or provided in connection with a coach or other end user’s (“you” or “your”) use of the <%= link_to 'www.mystepsapp.com', root_path, target: "_blank" %> website and the services made available by us through that website or through downloadable applications (an “App”) we make available to you (collectively, the website and the App, the “Website”).  This Policy applies solely to information collected by or in connection with the Website.  This Policy does not apply to the practices of companies that Right Side does not administer, or to individuals that Right Side does not employ.  Your access and use of the Website is subject to this Policy and to our separate Terms of Service [LINK]. Capitalized terms used but not defined in this Policy have the meaning assigned to them in the Terms of Service.</p>
			<p>The Website and Services enable a health, wellness or other coach, which may be a gym instructor, dietitian, physical therapist, life coach, executive coach or other health provider (a “Coach”), to collect data about certain behaviors or activities of end users (“End Users”) that those End Users choose to track through their mobile devices in combination with personal information submitted by those End Users to us in order to provide those End Users with notices and feedback to help the End User try to maintain or achieve certain behavioral goals, such as following a diet, exercise or health plan.  End Users may either self-report data through the Services or the data may be automatically collected by the End User’s mobile device (such as GPS, accelerometers, etc.) (any personal data about you submitted or collected through the Website, your “App Data”).  Through our Services, an End User can receive push notifications of reminders or metrics regarding certain behaviors that the End User chooses to track through the Services.  Our Service may permit an End User to disclose the End User’s App Data to a third party from time to time; provided that the End User does so at the End User’s own risk.  In order to use the Services, you must have a mobile device enabled with our downloadable application, or use the Services through a computer that can access our Website.</p>
			<p>Right Side does not knowingly collect information from children under 13.  If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child under the age of 13 has used our Services and provided personally identifiable information to us, please contact us at contact@rightsidehealth.com and we will work to delete that account and any such personally identifiable information.</p>
			<ol>
				<li>
					<p class="heading">Effective Date; Changes.</p>
					<p>This Policy applies to all information collected by or provided to us on and after the Effective Date.  When we make any material changes to this Policy, we will change the Effective Date above and will inform you by e-mail sent to the address associated with your account, through a push notification in our App or through the App the next time you log in.  We will treat your continued use of the App following such notice as your acceptance of the changes.  However, to the extent required by applicable law, we will seek your affirmative consent prior to applying any material change to this Policy to information we collected or received prior to the date of the change.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p class="heading">Third Parties.</p>
					<p>We may offer links to third parties’ websites or services through the Website.  This Policy does not apply to information that you may provide to or that may be collected by third parties.  We encourage you to request such third parties to provide you with their applicable privacy policies and other terms and conditions before participating in their services or making a purchase.</p>
					<p>If you are a Coach, you shall provide any End User with whom you use the Website the protections provided in this Policy or you may provide an End User with a separate privacy policy reflecting your privacy practices.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p class="heading">Collected Information.</p>
					<p><span class="bold">Overview.</span>  Our primary purpose in collecting Personal Information (as defined below) is to provide you with a smooth, efficient, and customized experience using our Website.  This allows us to provide services and features that are more likely to meet your needs, and to customize our Website to improve your experience.  As used herein, "Personal Information" means information that specifically identifies an individual (such as a name, address, or e-mail address, etc.) or other information about that individual that is directly linked to Personal Information.  Personal Information does not include "aggregate" information, which is non-personally identifiable data we collect or derive about the use or performance of our Website, or “de-identified data”, which is information after we have reasonably removed the ability to identify an individual from such data.  We may collect and store information, including Personal Information, that you provide to us when using the Website.  We may use Personal Information to improve the delivery of our Website, including advertising, and to develop analytics and aggregated data that allow us and our partners to improve our Services and correspond with you.  We may de-identify data and use the de-identified data primarily for the purpose of improving our Services, but we may also use it for other purposes.</p>
					<p>We may also collect and store non-personally identifiable information that is automatically generated when you use the Website.  We use this information to do internal research on our users’ demographics, interests, and behavior to better understand, protect and serve you and our community.  We use the non-personally identifiable information, such as your mobile carrier, device and application IDs, and the nature of your use of the Website, to improve our Website delivery, including advertising, and to develop analytics and aggregated data that allow us and our partners to use our Website and reach out to you via our Website or otherwise.</p>
					<p><span class="bold">Information You Submit.</span>  If you create an account with the Website, we may collect the Personal Information you provide in the registration form.  This information may include your name, e-mail address and password.  We use this information to contact you about our Services in which you have expressed interest.  If you pay for premium services through the Website that we may offer from time to time, we will collect the billing information associated with the payment instrument you select or we may use a third party to collect such information.</p>
					<p>If you are accessing the Website through a relationship you have with your Coach, we may share your Personal Information that you submit to us with your Coach.  We will not share your Personal Information with a Coach other than your Coach without your authorization. You may withdraw the authorization for a Coach to see your Personal Information using our Website at any time by contacting us at contact@rightsidehealth.com.  Even if you withdraw your authorization with us, however, your Coach may have archived your Personal Information.  If you would like your Coach to remove your Personal Information, you should notify your Coach.</p>
					<p><span class="bold">Information Collected When You Use the App.</span>  When you use the Website, we may gather certain non-personally identifiable information from you, and this information may be associated with the Personal Information that you provide.  This includes usage information, such as information on when, how often and for how long you use the Website, and server log data such as a device’s IP address, MAC address and operating system version.  We may use a third party service such as Google Analytics to collect this data.</p>
					<p><span class="bold">Mobile Device IDs.</span>  We may create a unique, random alphanumeric identifier and associate it with your device and the information about you on our servers.  We may use this identifier to recognize and remember your device and your preferences when you use an App.  If you have elected to receive push notifications, we may collect your device’s unique token to enable us to send such notifications through the third party push notification services.</p>
					<p><span class="bold">Location-Based Information.</span>  If you allow location-based tracking through your mobile device and App preferences, we will receive information regarding your precise location (using the GPS antenna within your device) when the App is running on your device.  We may also receive information from the compass on your mobile device, including course, velocity and altitude.  This allows the App to track your location, and enables the App to send you notifications based on your location. We may also use the location to determine what advertising should be shown in connection with your use of the App.</p>
