				<li>
					<p class="heading">Data Security on Our Website.</p>
					<p>Right Side takes reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect the security of our users’ information, which includes encryption standard to the technology industry. If you have any questions about the security on our servers, you can send an email to contact@rightsidehealth.com.  Right Side provides the following security measures to protect the privacy of your health information:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>We require both a personal username (log-in name) and a password in order for users to access their information, and, in the case of Coaches, the information of their End Users.</li>
						<li>We use SSL encryption for data that is being transferred.</li>
						<li>We use firewalls to protect information stored on our servers.</li>
						<li>We limit the number of Right Side employees who have potential access to your health information.</li>
						<li>We limit access to your health information to authorized users.</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Despite our measures to protect your health information, there is always some risk that an unauthorized third party may find a way around our security systems.  There is also a risk that transmissions of your information over the Internet may be intercepted. If you provide your user name and password to other people or if you use a public computer that does not log you off our Website, your data is no longer protected. Please do not share your Right Side login credentials and use automatic screen locking features on your mobile device.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p class="heading">Deleting Your Information.</p>
					<p>You may at any time cancel your account and request that we delete from our servers all of your Personal Information by emailing contact@rightsidehealth.com.  Such requests will be honored within a reasonable time period after they have been received, provided that you give us all reasonably necessary information and cooperation.  Certain Personal Information may continue to be stored in our backup systems until regularly scheduled deletions occur.  In addition, you may withdraw the authorization for a Coach to see your Personal Information, as specified above.  You agree that Right Side has the perpetual right to use aggregate, de-identified information for any purpose.</p>
					<p>Please keep in mind that whenever you voluntarily make your Personal Information or other private information available for viewing by third parties online – for example on discussion boards or  forums, or through social networking websites – that information can be seen, collected and used by others besides us.  We cannot be responsible for any unauthorized third-party use of such information.</p>
